Thomas F. HANLEY, as Receiver of The Ozone Park National Bank of New York, Appellee, v. Chester H. CORWIN, Appellant. No. 322. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 5, 1937. William V. Hagendorn, of Brooklyn, N.. Y. (Frederick W. Beyer, of Brooklyn, N.. Y., of counsel), for appellant. F. R. Serri, of Brooklyn, N. Y., for ap-pellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment (IS F.Supp. 396) affirmed.
